slab
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a rough plank split from a log (perhaps still holding the general sense of slab ); often split slab of wood;  outside cuts, or rough offcuts, of logs (in early days, often used for rough constructions, hence slab-house, slab-hut).
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
